Termed as APUKIH in Sütsa (Morung) or boy's dormitory were centres where young boys after attaining the age of puberty resides to train about the ways of life. APUKIH acted as a centre for learning and education. Similarly Iliki was for girls, the name differs from community to community. The inscriptions on the APUKIH signifies unity, wealth, prosperity, warriors, bravery, and the ancient worship of stars and rainbows before the coming of Christianity.

A relaxing spot with walkways, sitting areas, nice lighting at night. Popular with nature lovers, tourists, locals and couples on date. 

Cheonggyecheon is an 11 km-long stream that runs through downtown Seoul. This spot is the Dongdaemun section of Cheonggyecheon. Not a piece of waste is thrown down though it is located within the busy Dongdaemun market. Cheonggyecheon remains fresh, clean and clear all year round.
